article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- — Dillon Bailey had 18 points in Wofford's 74-54 win against North Alabama on Sunday night in the SoCon/ASUN Challenge. Bailey went 7 of 11 from the field (4 for 8 from 3-point range) for the Terriers (3-5). Corey Tripp scored 12 points and added nine rebounds. Kyler Filewich shot 5 of 8 from the field to finish with 11 points. Donte Bacchus led the Lions (5-4) in scoring, finishing with 11 points. Taye Fields added 10 points and three steals for North Alabama. Corneilous Williams also put up nine points and six rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
